name: IEDExplorer w/ XML Parse
short_description:
IEDExplorer was created by Pavel Charvat and the original project can be found here:
https://sourceforge.net/p/iedexplorer/wiki/Home/

IEDExplorer is an IEC 61850 client tool written for testing and educational purposes. IEDExplorer can connect to an IEC61850 device (also called an IED) over MMS (ISO/IEC9506-1 and ISO/IEC 9506-2) communication protocol. The tool is written in pure C# including the MMS ASN.1 parser (based on BinaryNotes ASN.1 tool) and runs in .net environment, on Windows and Linux (Mono). 

This modified version can also parse a SCL-type XML file to create and display a logical tree similar to that created during communication with an IED61850 device.
summary: IEC 61850 client explorer and SCL XML file parser
